               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17511016-37-off168-c214" targOrder="Y" targets="t17511016-37-defend275 t17511016-37-off168 t17511016-37-verdict172"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17511016-37-off168-c215" targOrder="Y" targets="t17511016-37-defend277 t17511016-37-off168 t17511016-37-verdict171"></join>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17511016-37-off168-c216" targOrder="Y" targets="t17511016-37-defend279 t17511016-37-off168 t17511016-37-verdict172"></join>
         
               <p>585, 586, 587. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17511016-37-defend275" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Cronder 
                  <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend275" type="surname" value="Cronder"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend275" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend275" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
            , 
               
                  <persName id="t17511016-37-defend277" type="defendantName">
                     William 
                     Reynolds 
                  <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend277" type="surname" value="Reynolds"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend277" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend277" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
            , and 
               
                  <persName id="t17511016-37-defend279" type="defendantName">
                     John 
                     Russel 
                  <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend279" type="surname" value="Russel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend279" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-defend279" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
                
            , were indicted for <rs id="t17511016-37-off168" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-off168" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-off168" type="offenceSubcategory" value="grandLarceny"></interp>
               stealing one quart copper pot, value 12 d.
            </rs> the property of 
               
                  <persName id="t17511016-37-victim281" type="victimName">
                     Samuel 
                     Newton 
                  <interp inst="t17511016-37-victim281" type="surname" value="Newton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-victim281" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-victim281" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17511016-37-off168 t17511016-37-victim281"></join>
                  </persName>
                
            , <rs id="t17511016-37-cd169" type="crimeDate">October 5</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17511016-37-off168 t17511016-37-cd169"></join>. + .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17511016-37-person282">
                  Samuel 
                  Newton 
               <interp inst="t17511016-37-person282" type="surname" value="Newton"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-person282" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-person282" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t17511016-37-viclabel170" type="occupation">brasier and founder</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17511016-37-victim281 t17511016-37-viclabel170"></join>. I was at a neighbour's house, and one 
               <persName id="t17511016-37-person283">
                  Godfrey 
                  Arnot 
               <interp inst="t17511016-37-person283" type="surname" value="Arnot"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-person283" type="given" value="Godfrey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-person283" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             came for me there. I saw Cronder and Reynolds, and my copper pot; he charged them with stealing it; that Cronder took it, and gave it to Reynolds. Reynolds said they two had<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="175110160019"></xptr> been at the window, and that a third was standing at a little distance.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17511016-37-person284">
                  Godfrey 
                  Arnot 
               <interp inst="t17511016-37-person284" type="surname" value="Arnot"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-person284" type="given" value="Godfrey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-person284" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My master's next door neighbour came and asked me if we had not lost something out of the window; I looked, and missed this quart pot from off a rail; I ran down the street, and saw the three prisoners running all together ; I took hold of two, but the other got off over Tower-hill. Reynolds had the pot in his hand; he confessed that Cronder took it, and gave it to him.</p>
               <p>Q. to the Pros. How old are the boys?</p>
               <p>Prosecutor. Reynolds's mother told me he is between eleven and twelve years old. I don't know the ages of the others.</p>
               <p>Cronder's Defence.</p>
               <p>I am twelve years old next July. We did not take this pot, it was given us by three boys, who told us they found it in the rubbish over against the door. We took it, and went along quietly.</p>
               <p>Reynold's Defence.</p>
               <p>Three boys gave the pot to us. I don't remember I ever said Cronder gave it me.</p>
               <p>Reynolds <rs id="t17511016-37-verdict171" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-verdict171" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               guilty
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Cronder and Russel <rs id="t17511016-37-verdict172" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-verdict172" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17511016-37-punish173" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17511016-37-punish173" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17511016-37-defend277 t17511016-37-punish173"></join>
               
                     <note>[Transportation. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
            </div1>
